post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'True freedom of choice means that individuals must face the consequences of their actions, whether they are good or bad. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If an individual is already addicted, that would indicate they already have regular access to the drug.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The negative repercussions of drug use should be prosecuted on their own merit and context \\(without prosecuting the drug use itself\\).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will be seen as a sign of the government/authority giving up on protecting people from the harm they could do, to themselves and others, through poorly selected drug use.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drugs being illegal deters many people from using them. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The prohibition forces users, that are otherwise law-abiding citizens, into transactions with more serious law-breakers, opening them up for the possibility to escalate to more serious crimes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In many legal frameworks, the use of drugs is not considered a criminal offense. Only production, commerce, ownership and distribution of drugs are typically illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[A study](http://aic.gov.au/media_library/publications/tandi_pdf/tandi372.pdf) came to the conclusion that alcohol consumption was involved in 47% of homicides in Australia in a six-year period. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an appeal to nature fallacy. Nature is not the word on what ought to be done with its products.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use has a negative effect on freedom and, therefore, ought to be contained.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Most [drug users](http://theconversation.com/many-people-use-drugs-but-heres-why-most-dont-become-addicts-35504) can rely on supportive networks and loving families. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalising drugs would be damaging for public health. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "An Indian based study shows that substance consumption highly relate to [juvenile delinquency.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4919962/) That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without help some conditions could [worsen](https://deserthopetreatment.com/co-occurring-disorders/going-untreated/) to the point where they're a danger to others. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, [designer drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Designer_drug#Safety) posing as known substances - or being dosed wrongly - are a cause of harm. Legalization of substances with known characteristics would mean less harmful drugs are being used. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's entirely possible for the issue to be intolerance and lack of understanding from the family itself. In those cases, the issue is the reaction of the family, and not the drug use or drug users themselves. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The US government has [previously supported](https://www.ozy.com/flashback/when-the-government-said-marijuana-made-you-crazy/88232) the claim that marijuana use causes individuals to rape and murder others, or commit suicide. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [2018 poll](https://sputniknews.com/analysis/201809141068019139-uk-drugs-policy-children-threat/) reported that children find it easier to acquire illegal substances than legal ones.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drug legalization will stimulate local and national economies. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalized, users could be required to carry safe containers for syringes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Citizens would not have to worry about potentially losing their career over using a substance for a medical condition. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's easier to regulate established companies in a legal market than it is in the black market. Any issue would be with bad regulations, not legalization. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are insanely profitable at a relatively low level of effort, as opposed to other crimes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Opiates, such as heroin, are very detrimental to a persons health. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine addiction causes [higher impulsivity](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5817335/), meaning sufferers are more likely to engage in risky behaviour such as gambling. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without effective law enforcement, legalizing drugs might fuel criminal gang's economies \\(e.g., illegal trade\\). That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "If individuals are already addicted, legalisation just means they'll be able to get their drugs more easily, so they will tend to stay addicted."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not a matter of being "viewed as" criminals: under a regime of criminalisation, drug users *are* criminals. It is not a matter of "feeling comfortable" seeking help, it\'s that seeking help would no longer carry the threat of actually going to prison. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of this emotional harm is directly caused by erroneous negative perceptions of drug use like the ones being perpetrated here. Many people are unfairly vilified for responsibly using drugs, simply because they are illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization will facilitate access to drugs.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Lack of regulation](https://www.drugabuse.gov/drugs-abuse/opioids/opioid-overdose-crisis#three) has been a significant cause of the opioid crisis.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[High individuals](https://philosophynow.org/issues/113/On_Moral_Arguments_Against_Recreational_Drug_Use) know the difference between right and wrong and can understand when they are hurting others.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [global financial crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_crisis_of_2007%E2%80%932008) was caused by big companies acting with only their profits in mind, and the detrimental effects are still felt today. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would increase the probability of violence and offenses.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There are legal substances which have a much higher toxicity and legal substances which can be developed to be highly toxic. The possible use of drugs as weapons is irrelevant as there are much more dangerous substances freely available.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A significant number of individuals are already drawn to legal addictive substances, for instance, cigarettes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs means that they are taken, and disposed of, more safely and cautiously than in the current environment.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs may lead to children trying and becoming involved with drugs at a younger age.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments invested a lot of money trying to cease drug use by everyone. It failed miserably. Not only it is not the most efficient way, but it is not even achievable.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of the appeal to rebellious teens is the fact that drug use is illegal. Treating moderated drug use as a normalized behavior and treating addiction/binge use as disease takes much of the "cool" factor away. That\'s why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The pharmaceutical industry is far less dangerous or violent than the alternative of drug cartels. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If established companies behave inappropriately with regards to the selling of drugs, people would be able to report this without fear of facing consequences for trying to buy drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The lack of regulation surrounding prescribed opioids was caused by pharmaceutical companies [failing to divulge](https://www.drugabuse.gov/drugs-abuse/opioids/opioid-overdose-crisis#three) how addictive opioid painkillers were to the medical community in the 1990s.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This ignores proportionality \\(meaning how many people were negatively affected and to what magnitude\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The risk of MDMA is not higher than many sports. MDMA has been compared to [horseback riding](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk/7876425.stm) in terms of risks. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Creativity can be stimulated through the use of drugs. Drugs could help us to live in a more creative dynamic society.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Self-medication, for instance with [analgesics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analgesic), will worsen the disease and delay proper treatment. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If legalized, the users wouldn't have the same incentive to rid themselves of the evidence as quickly as possible."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If psychoactive medicine were properly administered and regulated, it could function in this religious/transcendental function, without causing personal and societal dysfunction. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'While it might be better for society if a corporation created a less addictive drug, the actual incentive would be to create the most addictive drug imaginable. The corporation would then patent this to own a monopoly and charge a huge amount for continued use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Evidence suggests that [addiction is not caused by drugs](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ao8L-0nSYzg) but by social problems.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During the prohibition of alcoholic beverages between 1920 and 1930 in the US, there were multiple negative impacts on consumers.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drugs are already easily accessible and quite expensive yet the alcohol industry is still flourishing. It doesn't have to be one or the other. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established entities selling drugs would almost certainly not engage in gun battles on the streets over "[turf](https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Turf)".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's entirely possible for the issue to be intolerance and lack of understanding from the family itself. In those cases, the issue is the reaction of the family, and not the drug use or drug users themselves. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalization improves government finances.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising strong opioids such as heroin would only exacerbate the opioid crisis.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drug users will encourage other people, who do not know how to handle drugs and/or aren't smart and/or mature enough to try it. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will decrease the number of fatal overdoses by giving each user a safe dose of the drugs by regulating the drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use is not the same as drug addiction.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Foreign countries' dealers might find it convenient to resupply in a nearby country where drugs have been legalized, thus boosting the phenomenon of international drug trafficking, expensive to track down and halt."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Nixon's war on drugs [was started](https://www.cnn.com/2016/03/23/politics/john-ehrlichman-richard-nixon-drug-war-blacks-hippie/index.html) to target blacks and hippies."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When weed was legalized in Colorado for recreational use, the [usage rate](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-colorado-marijuana-idUSKCN0Z702N) among teens and children stayed the same. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various governments have already facilitated access to drugs and positive outcomes have come of this.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization will facilitate access to drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Nearly all negative effects of addicts on their families are not fueled by the addiction itself, but the fact that the drug they are addicted to is made illegal by the ban on drugs. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legal shifts the focus of the police from investigating crimes where individuals damaged others instead of themselves. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's important to have a standardized quantity of an active substance of controlled quality to prevent overdosing unwanted effects. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drugs are already easily accessible and quite expensive yet the alcohol industry is still flourishing. It doesn't have to be one or the other. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Heroin users](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/what-are-medical-complications-chronic-heroin-use) experience mental disorders, such as depression, insomnia and antisocial personality disorder.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under legalisation, self-injection as a route of administration may be reduced, as safer alternatives become available.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The violence associated with alcohol was far greater during the prohibition when it was banned. The National Bureau of Economic Research says: "[increases in enforcement of drug and alcohol prohibition have been associated with increases in the homicide rate](https://www.nber.org/papers/w6950)".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs will improve overall safety by containing criminal opportunities.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs relate frequently with [suicide attempts](https://www.encyclopedia.com/education/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/accidents-and-injuries-drugs). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Removing some of these constraints through the legalisation of drugs could make studies more successful.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is better to educate people on how to use valuable-yet-dangerous things safely than to ban their use entirely.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Banning drugs is akin to what happens in the film [Minority Report](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minority_Report_\\(film\\)): it's arresting people for what they might do under the influence. We could as soon prosecute people for being out of work, drinking, gambling or adultery."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Governments manipulate citizens by spreading biased information about drugs and thereby interfering with their choices. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Thousands of people [are killed](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/mexicos-drug-war) annually by drug cartels.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This isn't possible with the most popular date rape drug alcohol, at least not in higher doses, as it's taste is quite unmistakable."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is not the government's responsibility to provide a safe place for dangerous recreational activities. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can be used to abuse others or commit crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
